{"formatVersion":"1","manifest":{"primaryCategory":"Mind & Well-being","subcategory":"Recovery","audienceTags":["theme:recovery","theme:resilience","audience:recovery","audience:morning"],"sortPriority":36,"groupingLevels":[],"groupingLabels":[],"dataPath":"Data/Collections/Sobriety_Recovery.json","supplementalDataPath":null,"languageCode":"en","displayNameEnglish":"Recovery & Sobriety","script":"Latin","isRTL":false,"transliterationAvailable":false,"contentRating":"general","sourceId":"sobrietyRecovery","displayName":"Recovery & Sobriety","version":"1.0","language":"English","edition":"Curated Wisdom","type":"quotes","browseOrder":"sequence","itemCount":250,"supportsRandom":true,"supportsBrowse":true},"data":[{"id":"recovery-000001","text":"Recovery is an acceptance that your life is in shambles and you have to change it.","author":"Jamie Lee Curtis","source":"Recovery tradition (attributed)","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000002","text":"I got sober. I stopped killing myself with alcohol. I began to think: 'Wait a minute — if I can stop doing this, what are the possibilities?","author":"Craig Ferguson","source":"American on Purpose (paraphrase)","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:possibility","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000003","text":"The first step towards getting somewhere is to decide you're not going to stay where you are.","author":"J.P. Morgan","source":"General wisdom tradition (attributed)","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:change","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000004","text":"Nobody stays recovered unless the life they have created is more rewarding and satisfying than the one they left behind.","author":"Anne Fletcher","source":"Sober for Good (paraphrase)","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:purpose","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000005","text":"One day at a time — this is enough. Do not look back and grieve over the past, for it is gone; and do not be troubled about the future, for it has yet to come.","author":"Recovery Tradition","source":"Twelve-Step Tradition","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:mindfulness","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000006","text":"Your best days are ahead of you. The movie starts when the guy gets sober and puts his life back together.","author":"Bucky Sinister","source":"Get Up: A 12-Step Guide to Recovery for Misfits (paraphrase)","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:hope","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000007","text":"Courage is not the absence of fear, but rather the assessment that something else is more important than fear.","author":"Franklin D. Roosevelt","source":"General tradition (attributed)","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:courage","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000008","text":"We do not have to think alike to love alike.","author":"Francis David","source":"Unitarian tradition","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:community","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000009","text":"There is no shame in beginning again, for you get a chance to build bigger and better than before.","author":"Leon Brown","source":"General wisdom tradition","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000010","text":"You are braver than you believe, stronger than you seem, and smarter than you think.","author":"A.A. Milne","source":"Winnie-the-Pooh (attributed)","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000011","text":"It does not matter how slowly you go as long as you do not stop.","author":"Confucius","source":"General wisdom tradition (attributed)","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000012","text":"Rock bottom became the solid foundation on which I rebuilt my life.","author":"J.K. Rowling","source":"Harvard Commencement Address 2008 (paraphrase)","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000013","text":"The road of recovery is paved with the footprints of those who chose to keep walking.","author":"Recovery Tradition","source":"Twelve-Step Tradition","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000014","text":"I am not defined by my relapses, but by my decision to keep going after every one of them.","author":"Recovery Tradition","source":"Twelve-Step Tradition","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000015","text":"Serenity is not freedom from the storm, but peace within it.","author":"Recovery Tradition","source":"Serenity Prayer tradition","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:peace","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000016","text":"Grant me the serenity to accept the things I cannot change, courage to change the things I can, and wisdom to know the difference.","author":"Reinhold Niebuhr","source":"The Serenity Prayer (1943)","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:wisdom","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000017","text":"Every day is a new beginning. Take a deep breath, smile, and start again.","author":"Recovery Tradition","source":"General wisdom tradition","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:hope","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000018","text":"You don't have to see the whole staircase, just take the first step.","author":"Martin Luther King Jr.","source":"General tradition (attributed)","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:courage","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000019","text":"Healing begins when someone bears witness to our story.","author":"Recovery Tradition","source":"Therapeutic tradition","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:healing","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000020","text":"We are not alone. We never were.","author":"Recovery Tradition","source":"Twelve-Step Tradition","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:community","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000021","text":"Very frankly, I am opposed to people being programmed by others. My whole approach in broadcasting has always been 'You are an important person just the way you are. You can make healthy decisions.' Maybe I'm going on too long, but I just feel that anything that allows a person to be more active in the control of his or her life, in a healthy way, is important.","author":"Fred Rogers","source":"Fred Rogers","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000022","text":"When I was a child and my mother and I would read about such events in the newspapers or see them in newsreels, she used to tell me, “Always look for the helpers. There’s always someone who is trying to help.”","author":"Fred Rogers","source":"Fred Rogers","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000023","text":"There was something else my mother did that I've always remembered: \"Always look for the helpers,\" she'd tell me. \"There's always someone who is trying to help.","author":"Fred Rogers","source":"Fred Rogers","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000024","text":"Isn’t it amazing how much human beings are able to take? I wonder what the breaking point is. But I always look for the faithful remnant. You think that everything is lost and nobody believes in anything that is healthy anymore and all of a sudden you find this faithful remnant of hope. It’s like my mother said, always look for the helpers. At the edge of any disaster, you will find them.","author":"Fred Rogers","source":"Fred Rogers","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000025","text":"You know, I think everybody longs to be loved, and longs to know that he or she is lovable. And, consequently, the greatest thing that we can do is to help somebody know that they're loved and capable of loving.","author":"Fred Rogers","source":"Fred Rogers","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000026","text":"Yes, when I was here the first word of the alma mater was 'Men…Men of Dartmouth, give a rouse…' Well, now the first word is 'Dear.' Some things change for the better.","author":"Fred Rogers","source":"Fred Rogers","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000027","text":"Our world hangs like a magnificent jewel in the vastness of space. Every one of us is a part of that jewel. A facet of that jewel. And in the perspective of infinity, our differences are infinitesimal.","author":"Fred Rogers","source":"Fred Rogers","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000028","text":"Well, what is essential about you? And who are those who have helped you become the person that you are? Anyone who has ever graduated from a college, anyone who has ever been able to sustain a good work, has had at least one person and often many who have believed in him or her. We just don't get to be competent human beings without a lot of different investments from others.","author":"Fred Rogers","source":"Fred Rogers","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000029","text":"When I say it's you I like, I'm talking about that part of you that knows that life is far more than anything you can ever see or hear or touch. That deep part of you that allows you to stand for those things without which humankind cannot survive. Love that conquers hate, peace that rises triumphant over war, and justice that proves more powerful than greed.","author":"Fred Rogers","source":"Fred Rogers","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000030","text":"I believe that appreciation is a holy thing, that when we look for what's best in the person we happen to be with at the moment, we're doing what God does; so in appreciating our neighbor, we're participating in something truly sacred.","author":"Fred Rogers","source":"Fred Rogers","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000031","text":"Vermont is a small state which makes an enormous difference.","author":"Fred Rogers","source":"Fred Rogers","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000032","text":"It's not the honors and the prizes and the fancy outsides of life which ultimately nourish our souls. It's the knowing that we can be trusted, that we never have to fear the truth, that the bedrock of our very being is good stuff.","author":"Fred Rogers","source":"Fred Rogers","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000033","text":"It's our insides that make us who we are, that allow us to dream and wonder and feel for others. That's what's essential. That's what will always make the biggest difference in our world.","author":"Fred Rogers","source":"Fred Rogers","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000034","text":"Little by little we human beings are confronted with situations that give us more and more clues that we aren't perfect.","author":"Fred Rogers","source":"Fred Rogers","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000035","text":"If only you could sense how important you are to the lives of those you meet; how important you can be to people you may never even dream of. There is something of yourself that you leave at every meeting with another person.","author":"Fred Rogers","source":"Fred Rogers","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000036","text":"As human beings, our job in life is to help people realize how rare and valuable each one of us really is, that each of us has something that no one else has—or ever will have—something inside that is unique to all time. It's our job to encourage each other to discover that uniqueness and to provide ways of developing its expression.","author":"Fred Rogers","source":"Fred Rogers","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000037","text":"Fame is a four letter word and like tape, or zoom, or face, or pain, or life, or love, what ultimately matters is what we do with it.","author":"Fred Rogers","source":"Fred Rogers","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000038","text":"Both Joanne and I can recall many times when we wish we'd said or done something different. But we didn't, and we've learned not to feel too guilty about that. What gives me my good feelings is that we always cared and always tried to do our best.","author":"Fred Rogers","source":"Fred Rogers","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000039","text":"Children are to be respected and I respect them deeply. They've taught me an awful lot.","author":"Fred Rogers","source":"Fred Rogers","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:compassion","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000040","text":"It is true, Logotherapy, deals with the Logos; it deals with Meaning. Specifically I see Logotherapy in helping others to see meaning in life. But we cannot “give” meaning to the life of others. And if this is true of meaning per se, how much does it hold for Ultimate Meaning?","author":"Viktor Frankl","source":"Viktor Frankl","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:meaning","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000041","text":"An abnormal reaction to an abnormal situation is normal behavior. p. 32 in the 1992 edition, , Beacon Press","author":"Viktor Frankl","source":"Viktor Frankl","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:meaning","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000042","text":"If there is a meaning in life at all, then there must be a meaning in suffering. Suffering is an ineradicable part of life, even as fate and death.","author":"Viktor Frankl","source":"Viktor Frankl","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:meaning","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000043","text":"There is nothing in the world, I venture to say, that would so effectively help one to survive even the worst conditions, as the knowledge that there is a meaning in one’s life.","author":"Viktor Frankl","source":"Viktor Frankl","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:meaning","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000044","text":"Ultimately, man should not ask what the meaning of his life is, but rather must recognize that it is he who is asked. In a word, each man is questioned by life; and he can only answer to life by answering for his own life; to life he can only respond by being responsible.","author":"Viktor Frankl","source":"Viktor Frankl","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:meaning","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000045","text":"What man actually needs is not a tensionless state but rather the striving and struggling for some goal worthy of him. What he needs is not the discharge of tension at any cost, but the call of a potential meaning waiting to be fulfilled by him.","author":"Viktor Frankl","source":"Viktor Frankl","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:meaning","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000046","text":"Between stimulus and response lies a space. In that space lie our freedom and power to choose a response. In our response lies our growth and our happiness.","author":"Viktor Frankl","source":"Viktor Frankl","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:meaning","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000047","text":"Viktor Frankl Institute Vienna","author":"Viktor Frankl","source":"Viktor Frankl","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:meaning","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000048","text":"Viktor Frankl Institute of Logotherapy","author":"Viktor Frankl","source":"Viktor Frankl","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:meaning","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000049","text":"Profile at Find a Grave","author":"Viktor Frankl","source":"Viktor Frankl","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:meaning","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000050","text":"Viktor and I, the Film","author":"Viktor Frankl","source":"Viktor Frankl","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:meaning","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000051","text":"Interview with Dr. Viktor Frankl on YouTube","author":"Viktor Frankl","source":"Viktor Frankl","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:meaning","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000052","text":"Viktor Frankl Interview on YouTube","author":"Viktor Frankl","source":"Viktor Frankl","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:meaning","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000053","text":"If the light were not in your eyes, dear Mr. Brooks, you would understand better how happy your little Helen was when her teacher explained to her that the best and most beautiful things in the world cannot be seen nor even touched but just felt in the heart.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000054","text":"One can never consent to creep when one feels an impulse to soar.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000055","text":"The only real blind person at Christmas-time is he who has not Christmas in his heart. We sightless children had the best of eyes that day in our hearts and in our finger-tips. We were glad from the child's necessity of being happy. The blind who have outgrown the child's perpetual joy can be children again on Christmas Day and celebrate in the midst of them who pipe and dance and sing a new song!","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000056","text":"The bulk of the world's knowledge is an imaginary construction.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000057","text":"We differ, blind and seeing, one from another, not in our senses, but in the use we make of them, in the imagination and courage with which we seek wisdom beyond the senses.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000058","text":"The problems of deafness are deeper and more complex, if not more important, than those of blindness. Deafness is a much worse misfortune. For it means the loss of the most vital stimulus — the sound of the voice that brings language, sets thoughts astir and keeps us in the intellectual company of man.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000059","text":"The only thing worse than being blind is having sight but no vision.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000060","text":"Our puny sentimentalism has caused us to forget that a human life is sacred only when it may be of some use to itself and to the world.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000061","text":"It is the possibility of happiness, intelligence and power that give life its sanctity, and they are absent in the case of a poor, misshapen, paralyzed, unthinking creature.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000062","text":"Strike against war, for without you no battles can be fought. Strike against manufacturing shrapnel and gas bombs and all other tools of murder. Strike against preparedness that means death and misery to millions of human beings. Be not dumb, obedient slaves in an army of destruction. Be heroes in an army of construction.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000063","text":"Self-culture has been loudly and boastfully proclaimed as sufficient for all our ideals of perfection. But if we listen to the best men and women everywhere ... they will say that science may have found a cure for most evils; but it has found no remedy for the worst of them all — the apathy of human beings.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000064","text":"When one door of happiness closes, another opens; but often we look so long at the closed door that we do not see the one which has been opened for us.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000065","text":"Believe, when you are most unhappy, that there is something for you to do in the world. So long as you can sweeten another's pain, life is not in vain.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000066","text":"Many persons have a wrong of idea of what constitutes true happiness. It is not attained through self-gratification but through fidelity to a worthy purpose.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000067","text":"No doubt the reason is that character cannot be developed in ease and quiet. Only through experience of trial and suffering can the soul be strengthened, vision cleared, ambition inspired, and success achieved.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000068","text":"Avoiding danger is no safer in the long run than outright exposure. The fearful are caught as often as the bold.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000069","text":"Security is mostly a superstition. It does not exist in nature, nor do the children of men as a whole experience it. Avoiding danger is no safer in the long run than outright exposure. Life is either a daring adventure, or nothing.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000070","text":"I do not want the peace that passeth understanding. I want the understanding which bringeth peace.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000071","text":"Some people do not like to think. If one thinks, one must reach conclusions; and conclusions are not always pleasant. They are a thorn in the spirit. But I consider it a priceless gift and a deep responsibility to think.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000072","text":"Alone we can do so little; together we can do so much.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000073","text":"Tyranny cannot defeat the power of ideas.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000074","text":"The most important day I remember in all my life is the one on which my teacher, Anne Mansfield Sullivan, came to me. I am filled with wonder when I consider the immeasurable contrasts between the two lives which it connects. It was the third of March, 1887, three months before I was seven years old.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000075","text":"Now, so far as I can judge, self-love is the root of all evil","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000076","text":"Virgil is serene and lovely like a marble Apollo in the moonlight; Homer is a beautiful, animated youth in the full sunlight with the wind in his hair.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000077","text":"I began to read the Bible long before I could understand it. Now it seems strange to me that there should have been a time when my spirit was deaf to its wondrous harmonies ... But how shall I speak of the glories I have since discovered in the Bible? For years I have read it with an ever-broadening sense of joy and inspiration; and I love it as I love no other book.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000078","text":"Ruth is so loyal and gentle-hearted, we cannot help loving her, as she stands with the reapers amid the waving corn. Her beautiful, unselfish spirit shines out like a bright star in the night of a dark and cruel age. Love like Ruth's, love which can rise above conflicting creeds and deep-seated racial prejudices, is hard to find in all the world.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000079","text":"The Bible gives me a deep, comforting sense that \"things seen are temporal and things unseen are eternal.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000080","text":"I do not remember a time since I have been capable of loving books that I have not loved Shakespeare.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000081","text":"I read \"King Lear\" soon after \"Macbeth,\" and I shall never forget the feeling of horror when I came to the scene in which Gloster's eyes are put out. Anger seized me, my fingers refused to move, I sat rigid for one long moment, the blood throbbing in my temples, and all the hatred that a child can feel concentrated in my heart.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000082","text":"There are moments when I feel that the Shylocks, the Judases, and even the Devil, are broken spokes in the great wheel of good which shall in due time be made whole.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000083","text":"Literature is my Utopia. Here I am not disenfranchised. No barrier of the senses shuts me out from the sweet, gracious discourse of my book friends. They talk to me without embarrassment or awkwardness. The things I have learned and the things I have been taught seem of ridiculously little importance compared with their \"large loves and heavenly charities.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000084","text":"If it is true that the violin is the most perfect of musical instruments, then Greek is the violin of human thought.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000085","text":"Toleration ... is the greatest gift of the mind; it requires the same effort of the brain that it takes to balance oneself on a bicycle.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000086","text":"It is wonderful how much time good people spend fighting the devil. If they would only expend the same amount of energy loving their fellow men, the devil would die in his own tracks of ennui.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000087","text":"No matter how dull, or how mean, or how wise a man is, he feels that happiness is his indisputable right.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000088","text":"It is curious to observe what different ideals of happiness people cherish, and in what singular places they look for this well-spring of their life. Many look for it in the hoarding of riches, some in the pride of power, and others in the achievements of art and literature; a few seek it in the exploration of their own minds, or in search for knowledge.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000089","text":"It is a mistake always to contemplate the good and ignore the evil, because by making people neglectful it lets in disaster. There is a dangerous optimism of ignorance and indifference.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000090","text":"I demand that the world be good, and lo, it obeys. I proclaim the world good, and facts range themselves to prove my proclamation overwhelmingly true.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000091","text":"To what is good I open the doors of my being, and jealously shut them against what is bad. Such is the force of this beautiful and wilful conviction, it carries itself in the face of all opposition. I am never discouraged by absence of good. I never can be argued into hopelessness.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000092","text":"I, too, can work, and because I love to labor with my head and my hands, I am an optimist in spite of all. I used to think I should be thwarted in my desire to do something useful. But I have found out that though the ways in which I can make myself useful are few, yet the work open to me is endless.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000093","text":"I trust, and nothing that happens disturbs my trust.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000094","text":"Optimism, then, is a fact within my own heart. But as I look out upon life, my heart meets no contradiction. The outward world justifies my inward universe of good.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000095","text":"But in a little measure my small voice of individual experience does join in the declaration of philosophy that the good is the only world, and that world is a world of spirit. It is also a universe where order is All, where an unbroken logic holds the parts together, where disorder defines itself as non-existence, where evil, as St. Augustine held, is delusion, and therefore is not.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000096","text":"To know the history of philosophy is to know that the highest thinkers of the ages, the seers of the tribes and the nations, have been optimists. The growth of philosophy is the story of man's spiritual life.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000097","text":"I see the clouds part slowly, and I hear a cry of protest against the bigot. The restraining hand of tolerance is laid upon the inquisitor, and the humanist utters a message of peace to the persecuted. Instead of the cry, \"Burn the heretic!\" men study the human soul with sympathy, and there enters into their hearts a new reverence for that which is unseen.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000098","text":"The test of all beliefs is their practical effect in life. If it be true that optimism compels the world forward, and pessimism retards it, then it is dangerous to propagate a pessimistic philosophy.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000099","text":"Who shall dare let his incapacity for hope or goodness cast a shadow upon the courage of those who bear their burdens as if they were privileges?","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000100","text":"We have found that our great philosophers and our great men of action are optimists. So, too, our most potent men of letters have been optimists in their books and in their lives. No pessimist ever won an audience commensurately wide with his genius, and many optimistic writers have been read and admired out of all measure to their talents, simply because they wrote of the sunlit side of life.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000101","text":"Every optimist moves along with progress and hastens it, while every pessimist would keep the world at a standstill. The consequence of pessimism in the life of a nation is the same as in the life of the individual. Pessimism kills the instinct that urges men to struggle against poverty, ignorance and crime, and dries up all the fountains of joy in the world.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000102","text":"Optimism is the faith that leads to achievement; nothing can be done without hope.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000103","text":"Capitalism will inevitably find itself face to face with a starving multitude of unemployed workers demanding food or destruction of the social order that has starved them and robbed them of their jobs.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000104","text":"Happiness is the final and perfect fruit of obedience to the laws of life.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000105","text":"A happy life consists not in the absence, but in the mastery of hardships.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000106","text":"It all comes to this: the simplest way to be happy is to do good.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000107","text":"If we spend the time we waste in sighing for the perfect golden fruit in fulfilling the conditions of its growth, happiness will come, must come. It is guaranteed in the very laws of the universe. If it involves some chastening and renunciation, well, the fruit will be all the sweeter for this touch of holiness....","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000108","text":"I am only one, but I am one. I can not do everything, but I can do something. I must not fail to do the something that I can do.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000109","text":"I feel that in this child I have seen more of the Divine than has been manifest in anyone I ever met before.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000110","text":"The greatest woman of our age.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000111","text":"I have been a great admirer of you always.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000112","text":"She will live on, one of the few, the immortal names not born to die. Her spirit will endure as long as man can read and stories can be told of the woman who showed the world there are no boundaries to courage and faith.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000113","text":"Whatever you were or are, you're a blessing!","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000114","text":"At the People's College in Fort Scott, Kansas, my mother met Arthur Le Sueur, who with Helen Keller, Eugene Debs, and Charles Steinmetz had founded the greatest workers' school in the country. Thousands of farmers and hillbilly men, miners, and other workers took correspondence courses in workers' law and workers' English and workers' history.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000115","text":"The two greatest characters in the 19th century are Napoleon and Helen Keller. Napoleon tried to conquer the world by physical force and failed. Helen tried to conquer the world by power of mind — and succeeded!","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000116","text":"I am charmed with your book — enchanted. You are a wonderful creature, the most wonderful in the world — you and your other half together — Miss Sullivan, I mean, for it took the pair of you to make a complete and perfect whole.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000117","text":"I need not go into any particulars about Helen Keller. She is fellow to Caesar, Alexander, Napoleon, Homer, Shakespeare, and the rest of the immortals. She will be as famous a thousand years from now as she is today.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000118","text":"No one is more welcome to the House than Helen Keller, whom we love. And she has a genius for finding words for great truths. Her comment on our busy programme was: \"Sympathy without works is like eyes without light.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000119","text":"The most wonderful being in America,","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000120","text":"No history of the world can be complete which does not mention Mary Helen Keller... whose overcoming of her blindness and deafness were arguably victories more important than those of Alexander the Great, because they have implications still for every living person.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000121","text":"Helen Keller biography & links at the American Federation for the Blind","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000122","text":"The TIME 100: The most important people of the century","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000123","text":"Brief biography at Pegasos (Kirjasto)","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000124","text":"Keller biography at The Royal National Institute of the Blind (UK)","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000125","text":"Helen Keller bio at the AFB Kid's Museum","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Helen Keller","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:perseverance","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000126","text":"There are thousands of people who feel that it is useless and futile for us to continue talking peace and non-violence — against a government whose only reply is savage attacks on an unarmed and defenceless people. And I think the time has come for us to consider, in the light of our experiences at this day at home, whether the methods which we have applied so far are adequate.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000127","text":"Ethiopia has always held a special place in my own imagination and the prospect of visiting attracted me more strongly than a trip to France, England and America combined. I felt I would be visiting my own genesis, unearthing the roots of what made me an African. Meeting the emperor himself would be like shaking hands with history.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000128","text":"For to be free is not merely to cast off one’s chains, but to live in a way that respects and enhances the freedom of others.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000129","text":"I hate race discrimination most intensely and in all its manifestations. I have fought it all during my life; I fight it now, and will do so until the end of my days. Even although I now happen to be tried by one whose opinion I hold in high esteem, I detest most violently the set-up that surrounds me here. It makes me feel that I am a black man in a white man's court. This should not be.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000130","text":"During my lifetime I have dedicated myself to this struggle of the African people. I have fought against white domination, and I have fought against black domination. I have cherished the ideal of a democratic and free society in which all persons will live together in harmony and with . It is an ideal . But, my lord, if needs be, it is an ideal for which I am prepared to die.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000131","text":"The ANC has never at any period of its history advocated a revolutionary change in the economic structure of the country, nor has it, to the best of my recollection, ever condemned capitalist society.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000132","text":"Difficulties break some men but make others. No axe is sharp enough to cut the soul of a sinner who keeps on trying, one armed with the hope that he will rise even in the end.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000133","text":"I like friends who have independent minds because they tend to make you see problems from all angles.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000134","text":"I have never regarded any man as my superior, either in my life outside or inside prison.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000135","text":"Only free men can negotiate; prisoners cannot enter into contracts. Your freedom and mine cannot be separated.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000136","text":"The cause of Communism is the greatest cause in the history of mankind becasuse it seeks to remove from society all forms of oppression and exploitation, to liberate mankind and to ensure peace and prosperity to all.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000137","text":"Experience is the best legacy men could possess and never desert in life.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000138","text":"I stand here before you not as a prophet but as a humble servant of you, the people. Your tireless and heroic sacrifices have made it possible for me to be here today. I therefore place the remaining years of my life in your hands.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000139","text":"Exercise dissipates tension, and tension is the enemy of serenity. I found that I worked better and thought more clearly when I was in good physical condition, and so training became one of the inflexible disciplines of my life.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000140","text":"We are deeply concerned, both in our country and here, of the very large number of dropouts by schoolchildren. This is a very disturbing situation, because the youth of today are the leaders of tomorrow... try as much as possible to remain in school, because education is the most powerful weapon which we can use.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000141","text":"Coloured communities would like to see coloured representatives. That is not racism, that is how nature works.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000142","text":"I never think of the time I have lost. I just carry out a programme because it’s there. It’s mapped out for me.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000143","text":"Death is something inevitable. When a man has done what he considers to be his duty to his people and his country, he can rest in peace. I believe I have made that effort and that is, therefore, why I will sleep for the eternity.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000144","text":"I had no specific belief except that our cause was just, was very strong and it was winning more and more support.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000145","text":"It is in the character of growth that we should learn from both pleasant and unpleasant experiences.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000146","text":"Real leaders must be ready to sacrifice all for the freedom of their people.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000147","text":"Friends, Comrades and fellow South Africans. I greet you all in the name of peace, democracy and freedom for all. I stand here before you not as a prophet but as a humble servant of you, the people. Your tireless and heroic sacrifices have made it possible for me to be here today. I therefore place the remaining years of my life in your hands.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000148","text":"The majority of South Africans, black and white, recognize that apartheid has no future. It has to be ended by our own decisive mass action in order to build peace and security. The mass campaign of defiance and other actions of our organization and people can only culminate in the establishment of democracy.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000149","text":"There must be an end to white monopoly on political power, and a fundamental restructuring of our political and economic systems to ensure that the inequalities of apartheid are addressed and our society thoroughly democratized.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000150","text":"Our march to freedom is irreversible. We must not allow fear to stand in our way. Universal suffrage on a common voters' roll in a united, democratic and non-racial South Africa is the only way to peace and racial harmony.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000151","text":"We admire the achievements of the Cuban revolution in the sphere of social welfare. We note the transformation from a country of imposed backwardness to universal literacy. We acknowledge your advances in the fields of health, education, and science.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000152","text":"We too are also inspired by the life and example of Jose Marti, who is not only a Cuban and Latin American hero but justly honoured by all who struggle to be free.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000153","text":"We also honour the great Che Guevara, whose revolutionary exploits, including on our own continent, were too powerful for any prison censors to hide from us. The life of Che is an inspiration to all human beings who cherish freedom. We will always honour his memory.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000154","text":"I must say that when we wanted to take up arms we approached numerous Western governments for assistance and we were never able to see any but the most junior ministers. When we visited Cuba we were received by the highest officials and were immediately offered whatever we wanted and needed. That was our earliest experience with Cuban internationalism.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000155","text":"Long live the Cuban revolution! Long live Comrade Fidel Castro!","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000156","text":"The three centuries of contact between the peoples of Africa, Europe and Asia on these shores have for too long been regarded as purely negative; as an object lesson in the incompatibility of peoples from different races, religions and cultures. Yet when viewed from another perspective, conflict can be a creative force through which the latent potential of a society is released.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000157","text":"As a movement we recognise the legitimacy of Palestinian nationalism just as we recognise the legitimacy of Zionism as a Jewish nationalism. We insist on the right of the state of Israel to exist within secure borders but with equal vigour support the Palestinian right to national self-determination.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000158","text":"South Africa needs all its people black and white; young and old; Christian, Muslim, Hindu or Jewish. There is a place for all of us provided we have the courage to work together to build that common future.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000159","text":"We stand here today as nothing more than a representative of the millions of our people who dared to rise up against a social system whose very essence is war, violence, racism, oppression, repression and the impoverishment of an entire people.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000160","text":"Because of their courage and persistence for many years, we can, today, even set the dates when all humanity will join together to celebrate one of the outstanding human victories of our century. When that moment comes, we shall, together, rejoice in a common victory over racism, apartheid and white minority rule.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000161","text":"I watched, along with all of you, as the tens of thousands of our people stood patiently in long queues for many hours. Some sleeping on the open ground overnight waiting to cast this momentous vote.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000162","text":"This is one of the most important moments in the life of our country. I stand here before you filled with deep pride and joy: — pride in the ordinary, humble people of this country. You have shown such a calm, patient determination to reclaim this country as your own, - and joy that we can loudly proclaim from the rooftops — free at last!","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000163","text":"Perhaps it was history that ordained that it be here, at the Cape of Good Hope that we should lay the foundation stone of our new nation. For it was here at this Cape, over three centuries ago, that there began the fateful convergence of the peoples of Africa, Europe and Asia on these shores.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000164","text":"The names of those who were incarcerated on Robben Island is a roll call of resistance fighters and democrats spanning over three centuries. If indeed this is a Cape of Good Hope, that hope owes much to the spirit of that legion of fighters and others of their calibre.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000165","text":"The people of South Africa have spoken in these elections. They want change! And change is what they will get. Our plan is to create jobs, promote peace and reconciliation, and to guarantee freedom for all South Africans.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000166","text":"Your Majesties, Your Highnesses, Distinguished Guests, Comrades and Friends. Today, all of us do, by our presence here, and by our celebrations in other parts of our country and the world, confer glory and hope to newborn liberty. Out of the experience of an extraordinary human disaster that lasted too long, must be born a society of which all humanity will be proud.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000167","text":"Our daily deeds as ordinary South Africans must produce an actual South African reality that will reinforce humanity's belief in justice, strengthen its confidence in the nobility of the human soul and sustain all our hopes for a glorious life for all. All this we owe both to ourselves and to the peoples of the world who are so well represented here today.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000168","text":"We thank all our distinguished international guests for having come to take possession with the people of our country of what is, after all, a common victory for justice, for peace, for human dignity. We trust that you will continue to stand by us as we tackle the challenges of building peace, prosperity, non-sexism, non-racialism and democracy.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000169","text":"The time for the healing of the wounds has come. The moment to bridge the chasms that divide us has come. The time to build is upon us.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000170","text":"We dedicate this day to all the heroes and heroines in this country and the rest of the world who sacrificed in many ways and surrendered their lives so that we could be free. Their dreams have become reality. Freedom is their reward.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000171","text":"Never, never and never again shall it be that this beautiful land will again experience the oppression of one by another and suffer the indignity of being the skunk of the world. Let freedom reign! The sun shall never set on so glorious a human achievement! God bless Africa!","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000172","text":"When a man is denied the right to live the life he believes in, he has no choice but to become an outlaw.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000173","text":"No one is born hating another person because of the colour of his skin, or his background, or his religion. People must learn to hate, and if they can learn to hate, they can be taught to love, for love comes more naturally to the human heart than its opposite.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000174","text":"Education is the great engine of personal development. It is through education that the daughter of a peasant can become a doctor, that the son of a mineworker can become the head of the mine, that a child of farmworkers can become the president of a great nation. It is what we make out of what we have, not what we are given, that separates one person from another.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000175","text":"A good head and a good heart are always a formidable combination.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000176","text":"I learned that courage was not the absence of fear, but the triumph over it. The brave man is not he who does not feel afraid, but he who conquers that fear.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000177","text":"In my country we go to prison first and then become President.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000178","text":"No one truly knows a nation until one has been inside its jails. A nation should not be judged by how it treats its highest citizens but its lowest ones.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000179","text":"There is nothing like returning to a place that remains unchanged to find the ways in which you yourself have altered.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000180","text":"You may succeed in delaying, but never in preventing the transition of South Africa to a democracy.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000181","text":"Any man that tries to rob me of my dignity will lose.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000182","text":"The victory of democracy in South Africa is the common achievement of all humanity.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000183","text":"The authorities liked to say that we received a balanced diet; it was indeed balanced — between the unpalatable and the inedible.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000184","text":"Prison itself is a tremendous education in the need for patience and perseverance. It is above all a test of one's commitment.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000185","text":"I always knew that someday I would once again feel the grass under my feet and walk in the sunshine as a free man.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000186","text":"I have always believed that exercise is the key not only to physical health but to peace of mind.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000187","text":"There is no easy walk to freedom anywhere, and many of us will have to pass through the valley of the shadow of death again and again before we reach the mountaintop of our desires.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000188","text":"I detest racialism because I regard it as a barbaric thing, whether it comes from a black man or a white man.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000189","text":"If you want to make peace with your enemy, you have to work with your enemy. Then he becomes your partner.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000190","text":"I am fundamentally an optimist. Whether that comes from nature or nurture, I cannot say. Part of being optimistic is keeping one's head pointed toward the sun, one's feet moving forward. There were many dark moments when my faith in humanity was sorely tested, but I would not and could not give myself up to despair. That way lays defeat and death.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000191","text":"I have come to join you today to add our own voice to the universal call for Palestinian self-determination and statehood. We would be beneath our own reason for existence as government and as a nation, if the resolution of the problems of the Middle East did not feature prominently on our agenda.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000192","text":"We know too well that our freedom is incomplete without the freedom of the Palestinians; without the resolution of conflicts in East Timor, the Sudan and other parts of the world.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000193","text":"I wish to take this opportunity to pay tribute to these Palestinian and Israeli leaders. In particular, we pay homage to the memory of Yitshak Rabin who paid the supreme sacrifice in pursuit of peace.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000194","text":"I was called a terrorist yesterday, but when I came out of jail, many people embraced me, including my enemies, and that is what I normally tell other people who say those who are struggling for liberation in their country are terrorists. I tell them that I was also a terrorist yesterday, but, today, I am admired by the very people who said I was one.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000195","text":"Let's hope that Ken Oosterbroek will be the last person to die.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000196","text":"It is never my custom to use words lightly. If twenty-seven years in prison have done anything to us, it was to use the silence of solitude to make us understand how precious words are and how real speech is in its impact on the way people live and die.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000197","text":"What counts in life is not the mere fact that we have lived. It is what difference we have made to the lives of others that will determine the significance of the life we lead.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000198","text":"We tried in our simple way to lead our life in a manner that may make a difference to those of others.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000199","text":"Those who conduct themselves with morality, integrity and consistency need not fear the forces of inhumanity and cruelty.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000200","text":"Education is the most powerful weapon we can use to change the world and is a powerful part of that world changing arsenal.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000201","text":"When the history of our times is written, will we be remembered as the generation that turned our backs in a moment of global crisis or will it be recorded that we did the right thing?","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000202","text":"You sharpen your ideas by reducing yourself to the level of the people you are with and a sense of humour and a complete relaxation, even when you’re discussing serious things, does help to mobilise friends around you. And I love that.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000203","text":"A fundamental concern for others in our individual and community lives would go a long way in making the world the better place we so passionately dreamt of.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000204","text":"Everyone can rise above their circumstances and achieve success if they are dedicated to and passionate about what they do.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000205","text":"I did not enjoy the violence of boxing so much as the science of it. I was intrigued by how one moved one's body to protect oneself, how one used a strategy both to attack and retreat, how one paced oneself over a match.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000206","text":"Like slavery and apartheid, poverty is not natural. It is man-made and it can be overcome and eradicated by the actions of human beings. And overcoming poverty is not a gesture of charity. It is an act of justice. It is the protection of a fundamental human right, the right to dignity and a decent life. While poverty persists, there is no true freedom.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000207","text":"The Gandhian influence dominated freedom struggles on the African continent right up to the 1960s because of the power it generated and the unity it forged among the apparently powerless. Nonviolence was the official stance of all major African coalitions, and the South African A.N.C. remained implacably opposed to violence for most of its existence.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000208","text":"Gandhi himself never ruled out violence absolutely and unreservedly. He conceded the necessity of arms in certain situations. He said, \"Where choice is set between cowardice and violence, I would advise violence... I prefer to use arms in defense of honor rather than remain the vile witness of dishonor ...","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000209","text":"Gandhi rejects the Adam Smith notion of human nature as motivated by self-interest and brute needs and returns us to our spiritual dimension with its impulses for nonviolence, justice and equality. He exposes the fallacy of the claim that everyone can be rich and successful provided they work hard. He points to the millions who work themselves to the bone and still remain hungry.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000210","text":"You will notice that France, Germany, Russia, China are against this decision. It is clearly a decision that is motivated by George W. Bush's desire to please the arms and oil industries in the United States of America. If you look at those factors, you'll see that an individual like myself, a man who has lost power and influence, can never be a suitable mediator.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000211","text":"I really wanted to retire and rest and spend more time with my children, my grandchildren and of course with my wife. But the problems are such that for anybody with a conscience who can use whatever influence he may have to try to bring about peace, it's difficult to say no.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000212","text":"It's a tragedy what is happening, what Bush is doing. All Bush wants is Iraqi oil. There is no doubt that the U.S. is behaving badly. Why are they not seeking to confiscate weapons of mass destruction from their ally Israel? This is just an excuse to get Iraq’s oil.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000213","text":"If there is a country that has committed unspeakable atrocities in the world, it is the United States of America. They don't care for human beings.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000214","text":"Israel should withdraw from all the areas which it won from the Arabs in 1967, and in particular Israel should withdraw completely from the Golan Heights, from south Lebanon and from the West Bank.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000215","text":"I cannot conceive of Israel withdrawing if the Arab states do not recognize Israel, within secure borders.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000216","text":"One of the reasons I am so pleased to be in Israel is as a tribute to the enormous contribution of the Jewish community of South Africa [to South Africa]. I am so proud of them.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000217","text":"We consider ourselves to be comrades in arms to the Palestinian Arabs in their struggle for the liberation of Palestine. There is not a single citizen in South Africa who is not ready to stand by his Palestinian brothers in their legitimate fight against the Zionist racists.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000218","text":"Free Nelson Mandela!","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000219","text":"We can only agree with the words of the great Nelson Mandela, that indeed education is a powerful weapon for changing the world.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000220","text":"I simply don't understand why the Nobel academy gave him a peace prize or why Charlie Dimmock and Alan Titchmarsh gave him a new garden. And I don't see why he should be given a statue in Trafalgar Square, either. If we're after someone who stands up for the oppressed, what about Jesus? I feel fairly sure he never blew up a train.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000221","text":"The epitome of courage and intelligence.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000222","text":"Most great instigators of social change have intimate personal knowledge of trauma. Oprah Winfrey comes to mind, as do Maya Angelou, Nelson Mandela, and Elie Wiesel. Read the life history of any visionary, and you will find insights and passions that came from having dealt with devastation.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000223","text":"When he was in prison I admired him for his moral strength...Of his period in power I can see few results. Apartheid no longer exists, at least to all appearances, but no one understands what the new government in South Africa is doing.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000224","text":"How can a man who committed adultery and left his wife and children be Christ? The whole world worships Nelson too much. He is only a man.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000225","text":"Nelson Mandela is, for me, the single statesman in the world. The single statesman, in that literal sense, who is not solving all his problems with guns. It's truly unbelievable. Truly.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000226","text":"All nations have iconic historical figures on whom they draw for inspiration and strength at times of national crisis. We have the icon and we have the crisis but South Africa tragically appears to be still too disparate, divided, and confused to know how to best draw from Mandela’s example to mould a new nation. That is the sadness of Mandela’s closing years.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000227","text":"He walked like a man who does not take the earth for granted. He took one step after another with obvious care and delight. Right next to him, Winnie Mandela stayed close, attuned and alert, and radiant.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000228","text":"It is hard to eulogize any man — to capture in words not just the facts and the dates that make a life, but the essential truth of a person — their private joys and sorrows; the quiet moments and unique qualities that illuminate someone’s soul. How much harder to do so for a giant of history, who moved a nation toward justice, and in the process moved billions around the world.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000229","text":"It took a man like Madiba to free not just the prisoner, but the jailer as well to show that you must trust others so that they may trust you; to teach that reconciliation is not a matter of ignoring a cruel past, but a means of confronting it with inclusion and generosity and truth. He changed laws, but he also changed hearts.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000230","text":"Nelson Mandela – Biography at Nobelprize.org","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000231","text":"The Mandela Page at ANC","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000232","text":"Mandela: An Audio History","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000233","text":"Complete speech from the Live 8 concert","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000234","text":"Nelson Mandela Foundation - 46664","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000235","text":"Nelson Mandela Children's Fund","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000236","text":"Nelson Mandela at Writespirit.Net","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000237","text":"Nelson Mandela Quotes Video","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000238","text":"Quotes By Nelson Mandela","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Nelson Mandela","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","theme:resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000239","text":"Apartheid is as evil, as immoral, as un-Christian, in my view, as Nazism. And in my view, the Reagan administration’s support and collaboration with it is equally immoral, evil and totally un-Christian, without remainder. (Washington, D.C. 1984)","author":"Desmond Tutu","source":"Desmond Tutu","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:forgiveness","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000240","text":"If you are neutral in situations of injustice, you have chosen the side of the oppressor. If an elephant has its foot on the tail of a mouse and you say that you are neutral, the mouse will not appreciate your neutrality.","author":"Desmond Tutu","source":"Desmond Tutu","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:forgiveness","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000241","text":"I am fifty-two years of age. I am a bishop in the Anglican Church, and a few people might be constrained to say that I was reasonably responsible. In the land of my birth I cannot vote, whereas a young person of eighteen can vote. And why? Because he or she possesses that wonderful biological attribute — a white skin.","author":"Desmond Tutu","source":"Desmond Tutu","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:forgiveness","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000242","text":"Be nice to the whites, they need you to rediscover their humanity.","author":"Desmond Tutu","source":"Desmond Tutu","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:forgiveness","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000243","text":"I am a leader by default, only because nature does not allow a vacuum.","author":"Desmond Tutu","source":"Desmond Tutu","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:forgiveness","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000244","text":"History, like beauty, depends largely on the beholder, so when you read that, for example, David Livingstone discovered the Victoria Falls, you might be forgiven for thinking that there was nobody around the Falls until Livingstone arrived on the scene.","author":"Desmond Tutu","source":"Desmond Tutu","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:forgiveness","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000245","text":"Freedom and liberty lose out by default because good people are not vigilant.","author":"Desmond Tutu","source":"Desmond Tutu","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:forgiveness","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000246","text":"Children are a wonderful gift. They have an extraordinary capacity to see into the heart of things and to expose sham and humbug for what they are.","author":"Desmond Tutu","source":"Desmond Tutu","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:forgiveness","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000247","text":"For goodness sake, will they hear, will white people hear what we are trying to say? Please, all we are asking you to do is to recognize that we are humans, too.","author":"Desmond Tutu","source":"Desmond Tutu","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:forgiveness","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000248","text":"When a pile of cups is tottering on the edge of the table and you warn that they will crash to the ground, in South Africa you are blamed when that happens.","author":"Desmond Tutu","source":"Desmond Tutu","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:forgiveness","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000249","text":"I am not interested in picking up crumbs of compassion thrown from the table of someone who considers himself my master. I want the full menu of rights.","author":"Desmond Tutu","source":"Desmond Tutu","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:forgiveness","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false},{"id":"recovery-000250","text":"Those who invest in South Africa should not think they are doing us a favor; they are here for what they get out of our cheap and abundant labor, and they should know that they are buttressing one of the most vicious systems.","author":"Desmond Tutu","source":"Desmond Tutu","tags":["audience:morning","audience:recovery","language:en","theme:forgiveness","theme:recovery","theme:recovery,resilience","tradition:secular"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"isAffirmation":false}]}